# Technical lessons

Non-obvious technical gotchas, traps, and patterns that **can't be derived by reading the code**. Append-only — add new entries at the top. Each entry is dated.

> Don't write here: solutions to specific bugs (the commit/PR is enough), conventions already visible in the code, anything a test already covers, or anything that will be stale in 6 months (library versions, env-specific config).

> Write here: something that would cost the next contributor real time (>30 min) to rediscover, and that stays true regardless of who's reading it.

> For a dated **event** (an incident with timeline, impact, root cause) rather than a general lesson: see [`incidents/`](incidents/README.md).

